Meatloaf
source|Jenelle Yost
url|
aliases|
tags|
activeTime|
totalTime|1:30
yield|8 servings
description|

# ingredients
[Loaf]
1||egg (Beaten)
1/2|cup|Oats
1/3|cup|Milk
1/4|cup|Ketchup
1/4|cup|Onion (Chopped)
1|tsp|Yellow Mustard
1|tsp|Salt
1/4|tsp|Black Pepper
1|lb|Ground Turkey
[Sauce]
1/3|cup|Ketchup
3|tbsp|Brown Sugar
2|tsp|Yellow Mustard

# instructions
[Loaf]
Preheat oven to 350 degrees
In a large bowl, combine egg, oats, milk, ketchup, onion, 1 tsp mustard, salt, and pepper
Add ground turkey and mix well
Form into a football shaped loaf and place in a shallow baking pan/broiler pan
Place pan in oven and bake for 30 minutes
[Sauce]
Stir together 1/3 cup ketchup, brown sugar, and the 2 tsp mustard
Spread topping over meatloaf
Bake for an additional 45 minutes
Let stand for 10 minutes after taking out of oven before slicing
** If you choose to omit the sauce topping, just bake the meatloaf for 1:15 hr
